  "text": "## Grafana v38 Dashboard Migration Field Config Loss Bug - Root Cause Analysis\n\n### Summary\nThe v38 dashboard migration silently drops table panel field override configuration for dashboards without explicit `fieldConfig.defaults.custom`. The root cause is a flawed conditional in the cleanup phase that fails to preserve fieldConfig when custom properties are added during migration but weren't present in the original input.\n\n### Root Cause Location\n**File:** `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/frontend_defaults.go`  \n**Function:** `filterDefaultValues`  \n**Line:** 608  \n**Flawed Conditional Expression:** `if panel[\"_originallyHadFieldConfigCustom\"] == true {`\n\n### The Bug\nThe condition on line 608 only preserves `fieldConfig` if the panel **originally had** `fieldConfig.defaults.custom` in the input JSON. However, dashboards can gain `custom` properties during schema migrations (specifically during v38 when processing field overrides with `custom.displayMode`). When a dashboard never originally had `defaults.custom`, the `_originallyHadFieldConfigCustom` flag is not set, causing the conditional to fail and the entire `fieldConfig` to be deleted at line 620.\n\n### Failure Scenario\n1. **Input Dashboard:** Has `fieldConfig.defaults: {}` (empty, no custom) with `fieldConfig.overrides` containing `custom.displayMode` properties\n2. **v38 Migration:** `processPanelsV38()` converts `custom.displayMode` to `custom.cellOptions` in the overrides\n3. **Cleanup Phase:** `filterDefaultValues()` checks `_originallyHadFieldConfigCustom` flag\n4. **Condition Fails:** Flag is not set (original input had no custom), so condition at line 608 evaluates to false\n5. **Data Loss:** `fieldConfig` is deleted at line 620, losing all `custom.cellOptions` properties added by v38\n6. **Result:** Dashboard loses column widths, text alignment, and other custom field configurations stored in overrides\n\n### What the Conditional Should Check\nThe condition should preserve `fieldConfig` if **either**:\n1. The panel originally had `fieldConfig.defaults.custom` (current check: `_originallyHadFieldConfigCustom == true`), **OR**\n2. The panel currently has `defaults.custom` (added during migration) - **THIS CHECK IS MISSING**\n\nThe corrected logic should check if `custom` exists in the current fieldConfig structure, not just whether it existed in the original input.\n\n### Implementation Chain\n1. **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go (line 74):** Registers V38 migration\n2. **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v38.go (V38 function):** Initiates migration via `processPanelsV38()`\n3. **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v38.go (processPanelsV38):** Processes table panels and calls `migrateOverrides()`\n4. **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v38.go (migrateOverrides):** Converts `custom.displayMode` to `custom.cellOptions` in field overrides (adds custom properties)\n5. **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/frontend_defaults.go (filterDefaultValues):** Cleanup phase that incorrectly removes fieldConfig due to the flawed conditional at line 608\n\n### The Flawed Conditional in Context\n```go\n// Line 606-620 in filterDefaultValues\nif prop == \"fieldConfig\" {\n    // Check if we need to preserve the custom object before removing fieldConfig\n    if panel[\"_originallyHadFieldConfigCustom\"] == true {  // <-- FLAWED LINE 608\n        // Ensure fieldConfig structure exists with custom object\n        if fieldConfig, ok := panelValue.(map[string]interface{}); ok {\n            if defaults, ok := fieldConfig[\"defaults\"].(map[string]interface{}); ok {\n                if _, hasCustom := defaults[\"custom\"]; !hasCustom {\n                    defaults[\"custom\"] = map[string]interface{}{}\n                }\n                // Don't remove fieldConfig if we added custom back\n                continue\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    delete(panel, prop)  // <-- Deletes fieldConfig when flag not set\n}\n```\n\nThe condition should be inverted or expanded to also check if `defaults[\"custom\"]` exists **in the current fieldConfig**, not just whether it existed in the original input. A corrected version would check: `if panel[\"_originallyHadFieldConfigCustom\"] == true || (current fieldConfig has custom)` before deciding to delete the fieldConfig.\n\n### Files and Functions Involved\n- **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go:** `GetMigrations()` - Registers all schema migrations including V38\n- **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v38.go:** `V38()`, `processPanelsV38()`, `migrateOverrides()` - Implements the displayMode to cellOptions conversion\n- **apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/frontend_defaults.go:** `filterDefaultValues()` - Contains the flawed conditional at line 608 that causes field config loss\n"
}

